ENUGU – The All Progressives Congress (APC), Enugu Starr chapter has lamented over alleged exclusion of the party from participating in the poll. APC alleged that it has been stopped from participating because the list of her candidates were not published by the electoral body, even as it threatens to void the exercise if it holds as scheduled. The Local Government polls is scheduled to hold on Wednesday February 23, in all the 17 LGA in the state Osun Guber: Let’s Close Ranks And Eschew Bitterness,… Diri Bags Grand Ambassador Of Ijaw Youths Award The party alleged plot of the Enugu state Independent Electoral Commission (ENSIEC) of deliberate to disenfranchise the party faithful by refusing to publish a list of 260 councillorship and 17 chairmanship candidates it forwarded to the electoral body in December 2021. Addressing the party faithful at the state secretariat, in Enugu, weekend, the state chairman of APC, Barr Ugochukwu Agballah, declared that the party would void the election should the electoral body exclude APC from participating in the exercise. He said “Enugu must rise for democracy to thrive. There is no democracy in Enugu state; it’s been a government of cronyism and elitism… On Wednesday (February 23) the local government election will not be held; if they go ahead, it will be an exercise in futility,” According to the Chairman, the legal team of the party, led by a senior advocate of Nigeria, SAN, (not named) had already filed a suit at the State High Court to void the election for unlawful exclusion, which he said was a breach of the Nigerian Constitution and the Electoral Act.